<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT-365 Diesel Engine Diagnostics (2002) - ELECTRONIC CONTROL SYSTEMS DIAGNOSTICS - Circuit Diagnostics -
        Variable Geometry Turbocharger (VGT) Actuator
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Variable Geometry Turbocharger (VGT) Actuator</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <figure id="f24007" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="d3383" filename="../figd33/D3383.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px"/>
                <caption>Function Diagram for the Variable Geometry Turbocharger (VGT) Actuator</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The Function Diagram for the Variable Geometry Turbocharger actuator includes the following:</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Variable Geometry Turbocharger (VGT) actuator</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Electronic Control Module (ECM)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Accelerator Pedal Position sensor and Idle Validation Switch (APS/IVS)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Barometric Absolute Pressure (BAP) sensor</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Camshaft Position (CMP) sensor</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Crankshaft Position (CKP) sensor</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Engine Coolant Temperature (ECT) sensor</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Engine Gas Recirculation (EGR) sensor</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Engine Oil Temperature (EOT) sensor</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Exhaust Back Pressure (EBP) sensor</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Injection Control Pressure (ICP) sensor</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Injection Control Pressure Regulator (IPR)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Manifold Absolute Pressure (MAP) sensor</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Manifold Air Temperature (MAT) sensor</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>
                <title>Function</title>
            </para>
            <para>The Variable Geometry Turbocharger (VGT) actuator is a variable position valve that controls vane
                position in the turbine housing. The VGT actuator is located on top of the turbocharger. The valve
                position is controlled by switching a voltage source inside the ECM. The ground circuit is supplied
                directly from the battery ground at all times.
            </para>
            <para>The actuator control is achieved by setting a pulse width modulated signal in response to engine
                speed, desired fuel quantity, boost or exhaust back pressure and altitude.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>VGT Circuit Operation</title>
            <figure id="f24007" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="d3313" filename="../figd33/D3313.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"/>
                <caption>VGT Circuit Diagram</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The VGT actuator receives ground at terminal 2 directly from the battery ground terminal. The ECM
                controls the VGT by sending a pulse width modulated signal from terminal X1-18 to terminal 1 on the VGT
                actuator. Precise control is gained by varying the percentage of ON/OFF time of the VGT solenoid. A high
                duty cycle indicates a high amount of exhaust back pressure is being commanded. A low duty cycle
                indicates less pressure being commanded.
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>Fault Detection / Management</title>
            </para>
            <para>An open or short to ground in the VGT control circuit can be detected by an on demand output circuit
                check during KOEO Standard tests. If there is a circuit fault detected a DTC will be set. When the
                engine is running, the ECM can detect if the exhaust back pressure is equal to the desired pressure.
                When the measured exhaust back pressure does not compare to the desired pressure, the ECM will ignore
                the measured EBP signal and controls the engine with the desired value.
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>VGT Diagnostic Trouble Codes (DTCs)</title>
            </para>
            <para>DTCs are read using the Electronic Service Tool (EST) or by counting the flashes from the amber and
                red ENGINE lamp.
            </para>
            <verbatim id="f240dtc261">
                <line>
                    <emph type="bold">DTC 261</emph>
                </line>
                <line>
                    <emph type="bold">Output Circuit Check</emph>
                </line>
            </verbatim>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>DTC 261 is set by the ECM when the OCC test has failed after the KOEO Standard test has been
                        run.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>DTC 261 can be set when a poor connection to the VGT solenoid or defective VGT coil exists.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>
                <title>Tools</title>
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Electronic Service Tool (EST) with Master Diagnostics software</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>International&#174; EZ-Tech Interface Cable</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Digital Multimeter (DMM)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Breakout harness</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Breakout box</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Terminal Test Adapter Kit</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>12-pin breakout harness</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>VGT Pin Point Diagnostics</title>
            <figure id="f24007" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="d3313" filename="../figd33/D3313.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"/>
                <caption>VGT Circuit Diagram</caption>
            </figure>
            <table id="te24007083" tblwidth="pg-wide" frame="bottom">
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="2.00in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.86in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="3.00*"/>
                    <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col3" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <warning>
                                    <para>To avoid serious personal injury, possible death, or damage to the engine or
                                        vehicle, always disconnect main negative battery cable first. Always connect the
                                        main negative battery cable last.
                                    </para>
                                </warning>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1" align="center">
                                <note>
                                    <para>See truck Chassis Electrical Circuit Diagram manual for circuit numbers,
                                        connector and fuse locations.
                                    </para>
                                </note>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Actuator Circuit Resistance Checks</emph>
                                    (Turn ignition key OFF. Disconnect negative battery cable. Check with breakout box
                                    installed in X1 ECM engine harness only.)
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>X1-18 to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>3-7&#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Resistance through entire VGT circuit including actuator coil. Check with actuator
                                    connector connected.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Harness Checks</emph>
                                    (Turn ignition key OFF. Disconnect negative battery cable. Check with breakout box
                                    installed in X1 ECM engine harness only. Install 12-pin breakout harness to chassis
                                    and engine harness. Install actuator harness to engine harness only.)
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Test Point</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Spec</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Comments</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>X1-18 to 1</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>&#60;5&#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>If >5&#x2126;, check for open VGT control wire.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2 to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5&#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If >5&#x2126;, check for open VGT ground circuit.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2 to 10 (12 pin)</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5&#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If >5&#x2126;, check for open between actuator connector PIN 2 to PIN 10 on 12 pin
                                    breakout harness.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>10 (12 pin) to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5&#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If >5&#x2126;, check for open between 10 on 12 pin and chassis ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>1 to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>>1k&#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>If &#60;1k&#x2126;, check for short to ground in circuit between actuator
                                    connector and ECM PIN X1-18.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">VGT Diagnostic Trouble Code</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>DTC 261 = VGT actuator OCC test fail</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
